Presence of this file enables TEMPORARY tmux-powerline debug logging to
/tmp/tmux-powerline-debug/ — chasing the "status-right goes blank on a fresh devbox" bug.

What gets logged:
  runs.log        one line per powerline.sh left/right render (rc, byte count)
  dump.*          full env + stderr + xtrace for any render that came back EMPTY (max 40)
  main-tmux.log   traced main.tmux run at server start (catches errexit aborts)
  weather.log     every live wttr.in fetch (curl rc, byte count)
  snapshots.log   status-right/status-format option values every ~10s (who set it to ''?)
  server-env.PID  the tmux server's real environment (what #() jobs inherit)

To disable: delete this file (git rm tmux/.config/tmux-powerline/DEBUG && restow tmux).
Instrumented files (all marked "TEMPORARY DEBUG"):
  tmux/.tmux/plugins/tmux-powerline/powerline.sh
  tmux/.tmux/plugins/tmux-powerline/main.tmux
  tmux/.tmux/plugins/tmux-powerline/segments/weather.sh
  scripts/bin/tmux-claude-titles-loop.sh (calls scripts/bin/tmux-debug-snapshot.sh)
